{#-
  MARKER FIXTURE — Phase 12 Catalog++: the ATTRIBUTE-INTERCEPTION / CALLABLE dunder family.
  __getattribute__ dodges dot-access detection by fetching any attribute by name through the
  object's own machinery; __call__ invokes a callable obtained from a gadget chain. Both are
  obfuscation pivots a chat template never needs. The Phase-2..11 catalog did not list them,
  so this is MISSED; Phase 12 adds them to DANGEROUS_DUNDERS (GH-S001, CWE-94) and each
  access becomes reachable. (The string argument is a Const — never inspected, the identifier-only
  FP-killer — so the SIGNAL is the dunder, not the harmless 'name'/marker literals.)

  HARMLESS (the project conventions — MARKER only): parsed + walked, never rendered. The marker
  sentinel GLYPHHOUND_PHASE12_CALL_MARKER is a harmless string, not a real command.
  Sources: PayloadsAllTheThings (SSTI/Jinja2 __getattribute__/__call__ pivots); CWE-94 / CWE-1336.
-#}
{% for m in messages %}{{ m.role }}: {{ m.content }}
{% endfor %}{{ obj.__getattribute__(name) }}{{ gadget.__call__('GLYPHHOUND_PHASE12_CALL_MARKER') }}
